values:
i still cannot get over the atonement. i like the film but I LOVE the book. james, oh dear lord, james was good. i do hope that he'll win an award for this movie. i especially loved the confrontation scene with the sister, oh meng! he was brilliant. i rather find him short though, he even told the press that he is only 5' 7 and he is not a classic leading male star like brad pitt, hahaha! he is the same height as me.

part in atonement movie that really fucking kills me and stayed in my mind even when i sleep, was the narrating letters of robbie to cecilia.

**dearest cecilia, the story can resume. the one that i have been planning on that evening walk. i can become again the man that once walk the surrey park at dusk in my best suit, swaggering on the promises of life. the man with the clarity of passion made love to you in the library. the story can resume, i will return, find you, love you, marry you and live without a shame**

such a tragic love story, i love it! makes me a cynical person become optimistic when it comes to love, does that makes sense? i dunno. i did not cry on this movie but i cried like a mofo in the book.  ian mcewan is a brilliant storyteller and while reading the book, its seems like as a reader i felt robbie in me and how he is losing his soul each and everyday but the promises of cecilia are the one keep him going on. uff, medyo corny na ba? haha! i want to thank mr mcewan for perking up my literally obsession. i'm also glad that i have a friend who shares the same passion when it comes to reading and will start a james mcavoy appreciation group in facebook =p

ok, back to my old self...sorry, shameless post of my mcdreamy- JAMES MCAVOY! he is soo married that makes him so hawt, hahaha! ok obviously i wanted to wear a scarlett letter on my chest.

i swear i'm having those school girl crush again which is a good sign cos i complained before that i dont crush anyone anymore even movie stars. i guess, im not an ice queen of narnia....yet!

Pheew! my first ever post for a very long time.......

it feels kinda odd, it's kind of i'm in a computer rehab and i'm not allowed to touch any computers. work is really hectic, a lot of changes at work so i've been snobbing my friends and i haven't had fun in ages. so i've been very good except this time i have a new drinking buddy---- my mum.

after dinner, we usually have tea and some bikkie, but this time we have a glass of red each to help us go to sleep. hahaha! we're becoming alcoholics yo!

so me and my girls went out today, had dinner and watch a movie. we watched john tucker must die. i dunno, i can't find jesse metcalf sexy or even drool worthy. maybe i watched so many passions (don't ask!) before that i'm waiting for charity to pop out or that midget timmy.

it was funny though coz lately me and my girls were talking about how guys these days are so fucking retards. i mean, they are listening to their knob than their brains, right?????

i don't want to be discourage with this observations but WHERE ARE THE DECENT GUYS????  guys that are not playing games. guys who are honest and sincere. guys that find woman as a person with feelings and not an accessories. is my friend right? are they just bunch of dickheads roaming around the streets looking for a victim, make them fall inlove, hit them in the sack and then dump them. shit this is what i hate about singlehood, yeah its fun no boundaries, no ties pero puta the emotional part dude, nakakainis.

example na lang ha, like this good mate of mine (i will not name names) he is going out with this uber fashionista chick and really pretty. they're been going out for two years now and planning to move in together. they are basically married in bills ( ie shared car bill, telephone, accomodation) but everytime we are talking about how we meet a new bunch of hot girls and he's all going gaga and wanted to meet them. shit lucky i'm not that close to her gf or else i'll tell her about his dirty little dick.

i think guys stop looking to the other women when they are already in their bed pan or maybe when they go blind. i mean hands up those who think that your man is 100% honest with you? even when they are sleeping they are cheating on you. they are having wet dreams over jessica alba's butt or maria sharapova's leg. 

what i don't understand is what they frontin' on you. they pretend like they are the new age sensitive guys. like they are the victim of this ever changing world. i've been meeting a lot of guys lately who wants to get married, damn what is happening in this world? are the guys now becoming a sucker for romance? does tiffany and co targeting the late twenties male nowdays? if that was six years ago, i'll probably so aswoon and end up marrying some ass wipe dude, but i turned so jaded right now that romance does nothing on me. flowers-arghhhh! bulgari ring- fuck off. i listened to destiny's child so much that i surpass beyonce when she said "all the ladies who are independent, throw your hands above me".

my mum keep pushing me to get married that's why i think she wanted me to go back in phils and use my AUSTRALIAN CITIZEN charm to get a husband. she always said, " i can die now if i see all of you settled". then i'll answer her with "that's why i'm not getting married coz i want you to live longer!" i'm so terrible eh?!?

i always pray to God that i'm doing a right thing  about deciding not to get married. i've seen a lot of old lady at work who are not married (most of them are retired nurses-yikes!) and they are living alone and in some way miserable. i don't want to be grumpy and miserable but i guess i'll be like that if i don't break  this super protective barrier that no one can pass and hurt me.

i better stop thinking about this barrier bullshit again coz it made me think of this fucker that help me built them and he ain't worthed to be remembered.

hay naku enough with this bullshit, this is making me depressed. i'm still waiting for my romeo though, pero i think nakuha na rin sya ng bading :( :(

            BADANG AND ALANG WENT SHOPPING WITH VENGENCE!!!!!

i haven't seen my good friend marvie for a very long time, she is always busy and so em i. that's what happened when kids, family and work rule your world, for her anyways. i had so much fun yesterday, we went to quay to have lunch at doyles.  we didn't realised that they are having fashion show close to the docks area. we tried to sneek in at bettina liano show but you should see what we look like, hay naku! if not for our sunglasses, we both look like 1st class filipina maid of upper class family. it was so cold and we couldn't bother making ourselves pretty, shit eh what for pa.

shopping was such a delight yesterday, everthing was on sale speacialy in myer. marv bought this really cute 50's style dress in review. we also both went ga-ga over this really sexy cream dress by camilla and marc, pero leche i got to have sugar daddy muna kasi $760 yung dress.  

my aim yesterday was to get a weekender bag that i'll use in qld and a pair of boots,  just because winter came in quite early. i was going to buy this pink bowling bag in peter alexander but i was kinda expensive for a faux leather. so medyo fraustrated na ako kasi it's already afternoon and i'm still not carrying any shopping bag, di bah kainis yun? anyhoo...

so we went to nine west and check out some boots but my ogre size feet and calves are really not trying to get along with me, pero i found this really amazing oversized bag that fit two babies inside, so a big hurrah! may bag na ako!!!! 

malapit na kaming umuwi pero wala pa rin akong boots. i was really so fraustrated that i decided to just spend the money to something that always makes me happy- a pair of chunks (yung may polka dots na design)so we both went our way to mooks. luckily marv asked me to shop around muna in galleries area and thank God!!!! NU-NAN YOU ARE ONE SICK STORE!!! I LOVE YOU..... i found these
 last size na sya and was on sale!!!!! it is sooooo comfy, shit i can run a mile with this babies. ang dami pang shoes on sale in nu-nan, marv scored a ballet flats and i'm definately going back for this gold flats that i saw. oh, i'm so happy! it really made my day, good friend, good meal and good value, haha.

so tonight i'm putting this baby on test kung saan sya tatagal, i'm taking them out for dancing....YEEHAH!!

my friend rang me this arternoon out of the blue after he heard missy elliot "gossip folks".

so i decided to make my own playlist of songs in my pod that remind me of my childhood, highschool years and my friends. 

CHILDHOOD
thriller by micheal jackson- it was on the radio every fucking minute and i remembered being so freaked out to micheal jackson when he became a werewolf (noon pa freak out na ako sa kanya).
all out of love by airsupply- my mom love airsupply and she rub it on us. baduyfest but catchy.
staying alive by beegees- blame it to saturday night fever. my mom love disco tunes.
like a prayer by madonna- they have that hoochie dance comp in eat bulaga for this song and i remembered dancing along with them.
eternal flame by the bangles- oh my gawd i think i was in 5th grade and this is the 1st song that i memories by heart.

HIGHSCHOOL
tennessee by arrested development- when we came here in aus, this was the first song i heard on RAGE and i change the word TENNESSEE to PHILIPPINES. very catchy and i still listen to this choon.
killing in the name of by rage against the machine- haha, me and my friend create our own mosh pit inside mr may physics class when he doesn't turn up.
twisted by keith sweat- aray, i hate the memories of this song. it's actually a slow jam and we made a dance step for this song, yup we are lame.
black hole sun by soundgarden- 90s grunge at its best. i remember doc martens and not washing my hair.
criminal by fiona apple and down by the water by pj harvey- i cannot start my day without listening to pj and fiona. i'm was so full of angst thank god i'm over this phase.

FRIENDS
officially missing you(remix) by tamia- cruising burwood rd will not be complete if we don't sing along with this song, oh cres miss yah babe!
tempted by the fruit of another by squeeze- my bestie marv and i are OBSESS with reality bites when it came out. this is our theme song, she is winona and i'm janine garafolo.
nasty girls by inaya day- Ronald you fag, i miss shaking our ass together in this song.
one more time by daft punk- dieter my HOME buddy. 2001 mobile home at bondi beach craziest shit ever but so much fun. i miss you buddy!
insane in the brain by cypress hill- E, you can never be a gangsta just accept it, you're brown! i love yah man, thanks for ringing me.

i finally make use of my guitar!!(other than collect dust)

don't know what came up to me when i purchased this guitar, i don't know how to play it. i was doing some lesson back in highschool but i stopped it when my dickhead tutor gave me this frustrating "wala kang pag-asa" look. coz i play it on my lap like a piano and my fingers are really stiff like they got arthritis or something.
so i finally enrolled myself in a night school in bankstown and i'm hoping that i'll finish it and become a sick guitar player. i told my mom that if ever i'll be so good i'll leave my job and start a band. she told me that she see me playing in circular quay or inside the tunnel of st james station, thanks mom : (

sa wakas i'll be able to play MORE THAN WORDS, hehehe....

shit, i miss clubbing, hindi sa r 'n'b fuck i hate going there, those wannabe mofos really irritates me. i miss going to gay bar and see my "ladies". my good friend Taylor will be performing tonight and i won't be able to see him perform. he'll be copying RIHANNA, hindi na raw si beyonce, expired na raw kasi si beyonce, excuse me! no one mess with the booty lady. shit i wanna see the lasers again,  i want to dance non-stop. i miss going out until my mom call for search and rescue coz i haven't been home for two days. i miss my panda eyes every morning and driving home listening to MOS chill out session. i want to be 21again, i wish i'm forever 21 (shit di ba clothing store to?!?) 

i hate responsibilities, i hate getting old.

and i don't know where i'm heading
i hate this feeling.....

ahh...i love the air after the rain, it's so nice to be out on friday nights.

we were in burwood a couple of hours ago and we included ourselves to beautiful people in the streets of burwood. we have to wait for 30mins just to get a sit outside the resto, when did eating OUT become so IN? ok so we need to be outside coz we have to destroy planet earth with our nicotine but some folks in there are just wanted to be noticed even they soak up in rain, sorry but pneumonia is never cool.

oh, i have to post a pic of my very cultured godson BROOKLYN, who always order babycino with us and knows the different variety of coffee,true!
 this is his froth mustache. 


FEELING BLUE FOR BLUES FESTIVAL

why oh why do they have to do this every easter weekend. i'm a good catholic girl (lightning is striking me!) and it's part of our tradition to do some reflection every lent. so when i told my mum that i'm going to byron bay, naku i saw her eyebrows joined together, naging unibrow. can they just move this in anzac day or something, the line up is something to cry over if i don't go. imagine beth orton, david gray, public enemy, sir bob geldof, BERNARD FANNING, india.aire and THE AFRO CUBAN ALL STARS!!!!!!! OH MY GAWD, WHYYYYYYYYYYYYY?????

and it's in byron bay, i love byron bay. one of my fondest memories was when me and my friend went to byron bay before going to schoolies in qld. we were just checking what's the deal with this place and then we end up in NIMBIN. nimbin is a place where the hippies stay and when there's hippies there's pot, right, whatevs! oh man i was only 17 and my first time to go on a trip without my family, i totally let myself go. i nearly went home without shaving my armpits and got a dreadlocks, hehehe. 

oh, i'll do anything to be in blues festival : (

yesterday i woke up with a heavy heart and the weather seems to be sharing the same thoughts with me. so rather then making myself more miserable, i decided to go out  and take a walk. i always do this everytime i'm feeling down. in a way it helps me reflect on what i'm doing wrong and helped me eased my mind. this is much better than watching daytime soap and some crappy show in tv. 

so i head up in the city and walk around george, pitt, around cbd area then i end up in royal botanic gardens. thank God i did, when i got in the fresh smell of different trees and plants sort of lifted my spirit and made me feel better. i wished that i brought my digi cam with me so i can take better photo, i only used my phone cam. it turn out nice naman di bah?!?

THE ROYAL BOTANIC GARDENS


hehe medyo wonky :P

it's been a while since i been in this place, i think i was still in uni the last time i visited the gardens. this is my little corner, my little hide away.  i love sitting under this tree and read a book. i feel protected with the long branches that nearly touches the ground. i almost got lock in here before because i completely lost track of time.



they also got mini-river and bridges that lead to a rainforest area, you can also find fruit bat and different birds. i did chased this ibis who was willing to pose in front of my cam but changed its mind later.


there some unique and gorgeous flowers here. this place remind me so much of calaruega, damn i missed that place. i have so many fond memories in calaruega. the family loves to go there, it's our way to get out of polluted manila.



on my way out of the garden, i saw the towering building of my friends apartment, gosh i miss them. he used to make us smoke outside the balcony of his 36th floor apartment. eh takot ako sa height, so i rather die not having a fag. i feel like someone will push me from behind.




THE ART GALLERY


 i'm a fraustrated artist. my mom did not let me do art as she think it was a waste of time. so when i was in highschool, most of my subjects are science and all boring bullshit. my sister on the other hand (who btw cannot draw anything even a simple glass with water) did art in h/s cos this subject is for slackers, true. 
i always check out art express every year. when my sister have to pass a thesis for her art class, i was the one who made her paintings and drawings. it did not get in art gallery but was included in art express. it's one of my proudest moment eventhough my name was not printed on the work. she donated it to penrith council and i think it's still in there, i hope.

this are the few of my favourite art express........



 this work is so clever, it shows the game of love

 this looks like an ad for ipod eh? it says "you've got to be gay to get bi" hehe.


 ohh, this remind me of my good friend ronald. when he came out of the closet he doesn't want to go to work, all he wants to do was to celebrate.

 "LABELS ARE FOR FILLING, LABELS ARE FOR CLOTHING, LABELS ARE NOT FOR PEOPLE" damn right!

 this is a paul smith label with epileptic seizure, joke!

 my  favourite work of art in this gallery. my trip is not complete if i don't look at this one. this is  by degas " after the bath". i forgot the number of times i attempt to copy this and often i sit on the corner and just stare at this piece.

 another addition to my list. this is by ian fairweather and this is called "anak bayan". mr weather spend some time in philippines and he witness our tradional christening where the kid was introduced to the whole village. it is actually heart breaking cos you cannot see the baby  on this work cos  fairweather was abandoned when he was a baby.
 art class inside art gallery, i love it. i wish i can enrol myself in an art school so i can work in a gallery like this (kahit na cleaner, i swear!)

it was a productive day. i went home and was so tired i went back to bed.

i need a major body overhaul. two of my best mates are getting married at the end of this year and i'm one of the bridesmaid, ngeee! i'm going to wear gown. nakakatakot!!!

i skip half of my highschool prom coz the teachers was bugging me coz i turn up wearing a kilt and my doc martens. i have no kikay bone in my body and my friends know that, i think they are gangin' up on me.

so last night, i enrolled myself to mauy thai kickboxing lesson in the city for 8 free visits. this will be my first time to try this. i was doing tae bo crap in gym before but someone told me that this is quite intense. i think i'll just picture my boss face on the bag or someone who really irritates the hell out of me.

patay na naman ako nito!!!

oh yeah btw, tristan and isolde is like an adaptation of a mills and boon pocket book in big screen, such a crappy movie. i was so excited to watch this movie coz i love all that star-crossed lover type of movie pero it doesn't have anything that click my movie experience, the story suck.
talk about movies, this weekend just for fun
me and my friends are going to watch close to you ( movie nila john lloyd cruz and bea alonzo)in mt. druitt hoyts. this will be the first filo movie that we'll watch that doesn't starred by claudine and aga muchlach, hehehe.

i visited my old co-workers at my previous work and shop around in the vintage hub of sydney- crown street darlinghurst.
i missed this area. it's like a daily ritual for me to pass on this street and look around for some new, err old stuff in cc's flashback
and to granma takes a trip. so the way to my old work, there's this small cafe called vespa cafe and i saw those really cute vespa bikes.
shit i really want to own one but the thing is I CAN'T RIDE A BIKE. how sad eh?!? mom really deprived us, she wouldn't let us coz 
she really had a bad experience riding a bike and she doesn't want the same thing happen to us, pero the vespa, the vespaaaaa!!!!!


shit, this industrial law changes is really fucking annoying. i have no choice but to give up my weekend work and go back to m-f routine.
i gave up my weekend for bigger pay, less stress and 2days of not looking at my boss face, it is such a bliss. anyhoo, it's a good thing na rin cos
i can go to glebe markets on saturday and i can have a decent night out with my bitches, yey na rin!

i still can't forget those vespa =(

my co-workers asked me yesterday why i did not wore my green for st pat, i told them that i forgot and they just laugh off. huh??
i was known at work as the chick who always apply for leave every st pat and i'm not irish!!!

eh shit naman eh, i have brown/islander liver not irish liver so i have to look after them,tsk,tsk!

...anyhoo, the main reason i join lj is for the book club, gives me an idea what to read next and to be honest they are a big help in picking a good book. oh! i did not realised how beautiful jodi picoult is--see akala ko she'll be all geeky looking ( shit jackie, talk about stereo type) i dunno, i always got soft spot for red heads. i think she'll be coming here in sydney for book signing, i better find out more about this. i adore all of her books specially "the pact".

i'm still undecided if i'm going to do my masters in john hopkins uni. seriously who wants to live in baltimore maryland, di bah dito yung maraming pinapatay ng serial killer????? 
i'm doing my master for mental health (so i can cure myself, joke!) and they told me that jhu got the best teaching program for this, but when i found out that the hospital we're going to do the training, eh yung hospital sa silence in the lambs, ehhh nakaka-turn off. that movie scared the bejesus out of me. 

eh, enough of this blah. it's saturday and i'm in front of my comp- this doesn't look right, right??

My uncle is in makati med right now with busted aorta and the doctors said that they cannot do anything.

i couldn't help but cry, i feel so helpless, i hate being here in aus when my mind is back there worried about my uncle.

i'm losing a great uncle and a dad. when dad left us, he's the one stand in and help my mum raising us. we always turn into him everytime we are making great decision. he even walked my sister down the aisle when she got married.

i felt so sorry for my cousins coz it was only a year when their mum died. i mean, they are all grown up and have their own lives but i know that they still need him. i felt sorry to my mum, she never stop crying ever since she found out. she becomes so emotional when someone dies in our family and now someone so close to her is dying.

i want to go back to philippines just to hug her and reassure her. i know that she need us more than anything. my mum is so close to my uncle- to all of them. i can say that i never ever saw my mum, aunt and uncles have a fight, my lola did a great job raising them.

i wanted to kiss my uncle for the last time. i will surely miss his jokes, the smell of his cigarettes and how he always asks for coffee.
